hklscan                               macro                              hklscan

NAME
     hhkkllssccaann - general linear scan in reciprocal space

SYNOPSIS

     hhkkllssccaann HHssttaarrtt HHeenndd KKssttaarrtt KKeenndd LLssttaarrtt LLeenndd iinntteerrvvaallss ttiimmee

DESCRIPTION

     hhkkllssccaann is a linear scan in reciprocal space over the three coordinates HH KK
     LL which range from HHssttaarrtt, KKssttaarrtt and LLssttaarrtt to HHeenndd, KKeenndd and LLeenndd,
     respectively.  The step size for each coordinate is (ssttaarrtt --
     eenndd))//iinntteerrvvaallss.  The number of data points collected will be iinntteerrvvaallss++11.
     Count time is given by ttiimmee, which if positive, specifies seconds and if
     negative, specifies monitor counts.

EXAMPLE

     hhkkllssccaann ..99 11..11 ..99 11..11 00 00 1100 1100

SEE ALSO

